The paper discusses the application of machine learning algorithms for event classification in real-world contexts, specifically in the domain of human-object interaction in three-dimensional space. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for the machine learning aspect, cs.CV (Computer Vision) for the use of motion capture data, cs.LG (Machine Learning) for the development of the neural network models, cs.RO (Robotics) for the potential application of the research in robotics, and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) for the focus on real-world contexts and human-object interaction.
